data.title: Comida de Excellente!
data.text: I have eaten at this place for at least 6 years of my 20 years of being in Livermore.  I enjoy eating at this place.  ALWAYS good food, atmosphere, and entertainment.  Aye Carumba.  I HIGHLY recommend this place to anyone who wants to have quality Mexican food.  It's a hole in the wall, but a DAMN good one.  The Burrito's, Enchiladas, Chorizo platter, and most of the items on the menu.  Get a Sangria also when you go in there to wash it all down.  Get in there and enjoy Mexican food.

data.title: Best Chile Verde burrito anywhere
data.text: I travel. A lot. And when I travel I always look for the perfect chile verde burrito. I find some good ones. A ton of bad ones and now I have found nirvana. Nice chunks of tender pork perfectly seasoned. Served in a home made tortilla with the perfect compliment of rice and beans. Wow. I am sitting here wondering if I should order another one. But I think I will save that for the next time I am near. Do not miss this place. The food is spot on.

data.title: Great hole in the wall Mexican food!
data.text: The food is excellent! This place is always busy because us locals know if you want great Mexican food and service come here. There are two locations at opposite ends of town which is nice. Can't beat the price either.

data.title: I ate here once a week for 4 years
data.text: I lived just up the street. I have sampled most of the menu over the last 4 years. This is a consistently decent restaurant. The food is quality id good, the service is good and the prices are good. If you are looking for a budget friendly place with good food this is the place.

data.title: nice little taqueria
data.text: I love the carnitas, chili verde and carne sada. This place made me feel right at home not always the case when traveling alone on business.
